					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If I ever to make cartridges, they will always be 60-pins cartridges (so that I can use audio, and don't have to deal with CIC); an adapter can be used if you want it to run on a 72-pins system. In addition, all of them will work with NTSC, although some might work with PAL as well (I think PAL systems (other than Dendy, perhaps?) are always 72-pins, but using an adapter you connect it to NTSC and PAL).</div>

					
